2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an automatic motion assessment learning algorithm, which involves machine learning techniques such as time-segmentation, parameter relevance detection, and time-warping.
3. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper mentions the application of monitoring clinical rehabilitation processes, which involves interaction between humans (patients) and computers (Kinect cameras).
